subSubSection.paragraph:
COLORATION (
Figs. 152–155
). Color uniformly yellow to yellowish brown, only metasomal segments IV–V could be black.

PEDIPALPS (
Figs. 170–180
). The pedipalps are sparsely hirsute and smooth. The femur bears four to five granulated carinae, the middle carina on internal surface could be incomplete indicated by several strong denticles. The patella bears eight carinae from which internal and dorsal are granulated and other are smooth in both sexes. The chela is without carinae. The movable fingers of pedipalps bear 13 cutting rows of denticles, every with external and internal denticles present, and five terminal denticles.

LEGS (
Figs. 160–163
). The tarsomeres bear two rows of long setae on the ventral surface and numerous macrosetae on the other surfaces. Telotarsus ventral setation represented by long setae. Pedal spur of legs with solitary setae only. Femur bears only several macrosetae. Femur and patella with carinae well developed. Tibial spurs present and long on third and fourth legs and absent in the other legs.
